  "general_provisions": "This bill addresses the jurisdictional management of public lands.",
  "hilighted_provisions": "This bill:<hr><ltbullet>defines terms;<hr><ltbullet>asserts the state's jurisdictional interest in land controlled by the federal government under a proprietary interest;<hr><ltbullet>directs the Public Lands Policy Coordinating Office (office) to promote the state's jurisdictional interests on landscape-scale public lands; <hr><ltbullet>requires the office to:<hr><ltbullet1>identify and map landscape-scale lands in the state;<hr><ltbullet1>establish map layers for certain criteria on landscape-scale lands;<hr><ltbullet1> map a landscape public nuisance area on landscape-scale lands containing forested areas; and<hr><ltbullet1>report annually on the map to the Federalism Commission;<hr><ltbullet>requires the Division of Forestry, Fire, and State Lands to assist the office in identifying a landscape public nuisance area for landscape-scale lands containing forested areas; and<hr><ltbullet>makes technical and conforming changes.",
  "monies": "None",
